 final phase of the city between AD 62-79 . This is the first time that an attempt has been made to grasp the construction and equipment phases of the houses. However, the décor is not only classified chronologically, but analyzed both in terms of the décor decisions made for it and the effect of the décor.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aInterior decorationzItalyzPompeii (Extinct city). 4aArchitektur. 4aDekor. 4aRömische Kaiserzeit. 4aWandmalerei.  aRoman imperial age.  aRoman mural paining.  aarchitecture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023z9783111318110oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831110128340 cprintz978311100165440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111012735zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111012735zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111012735/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA